OL,3,CCourt shown footage allegedly showing
OL,4,Cmurder suspect disposing of body parts
OL,6,FIt is alleged in the footage, which a
OL,7,Fjudge has allowed to be released
OL,8,Ffollowing representations from the
OL,9,Fpress, that Mr Majerkiewicz made a
OL,10,Fjourney into Kersal Dale in Salford on
OL,11,F2 April 2024, to dispose of the first
OL,12,Fof Stuart Everett's remains. He is
OL,13,Flater seen to return with the bag
OL,14,Fempty and folded up, prosecutors
OL,15,Fallege.
OL,17,FIt is not disputed that Mr
OL,18,FMajerkiewicz is the individual in the
OL,19,Ffootage, but the allegation that he
OL,20,Fwas going to dispose of Mr Everett is
OL,21,Fdisputed, it is understood.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
